<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 05 at 5:17PM CDT  by NWS Little Rock</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Stone,
northwestern Independence and south central Izard Counties through
545 PM CDT...
At 517 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Croker, or 13 miles northwest of Batesville, moving southwest at 5
mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and half inch hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Cushman...                        Croker...
Herpel...                         Bethesda...
Marcella...                       Lafferty...
Saint James...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.50 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
